============================================================
IMPORTANT IMPLEMENTATION RULES
============================================================

- Do not use pseudocode.
- Do not skip files.
- Do not remove Phase 1–21 behavior.
- Keep all existing backend tests passing.
- Keep all existing frontend tests passing.
- Keep mobile tests passing.
- Keep desktop tests passing.
- Keep SDK tests passing.
- Use typed Python where reasonable.
- Use TypeScript types.
- Use SQLAlchemy 2.x style.
- Never hardcode secrets.
- Never expose secrets in frontend, mobile, desktop, SDKs, reports, proofs, envelopes, vault records, ledger entries, logs, docs, or exports.
- Never log API keys, KMS key refs, signing keys, private keys, runner tokens, broker credentials, cloud credentials, private payloads, raw prompts, or confidential evidence.
- Never store raw private keys.
- Never store raw confidential evidence.
- Never store raw prompts by default.
- Never enable live trading by default.
- Never enable real social posting by default.
- Never enable real IoT power actions by default.
- Never bypass Guardian risk checks.
- Never bypass content approval checks.
- Never bypass tenant isolation.
- Never bypass billing entitlements.
- Never bypass governance policies.
- Never bypass final GA safety gates.
- Never bypass data residency enforcement.
- Never allow agent quorum to replace human approval for sensitive actions.
- Never let revoked agents vote.
- Never allow release gate verification to pass if required safety, provenance, attestation, or policy proof is missing.
- Keep signing, confidential compute, vault, TEE, and ZK systems mock/dry-run/readiness-only by default.
- Keep all proofs evidence-linked, confidence-scored, limitation-aware, and auditable.
- Keep code modular and ready for Phase 23: autonomous trust-minimized execution, enterprise-grade policy proof marketplace, and cryptographically governed AI agent mesh.

